	<h1>Global Navigation</h1>
	<p>
		A main driver for user engagement,
		the global nav should be displayed on all of our pages to help tie the various products together
		and to provide a way for users to navigate the site.
	</p>

	<section>
		<h2 id="api">API</h2>
		<p>Content for Global Navigation is available in {{#link-to 'identity.api'}}API{{/link-to}}.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 id="interactions">Interactions</h2>
		<p>
			Design System doesn't provide JavaScript for handling interactions so you need to implement them yourself.
			The list of interactions for the Global Navigation:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Dropdowns — described on the {{#link-to 'route-components.dropdowns'}}component's page{{/link-to}}.</li>
			<li>
				Global Navigation bar behaviour
				<ul>
					<li>
						Desktop, logged in users — bar disappears when user scrolls down and reappears when user
						starts to scroll up, so far all products use
						<a href="http://wicky.nillia.ms/headroom.js/" target="_blank">Headroom.js</a>
						for that. When there is a dropdown or search suggestions open in the Global Navigation,
						then it should stay visible even when user is scrolling down.
					</li>
					<li>
						Desktop, anons — bar stays visible all the time.
					</li>
					<li>
						Mobile — bar stays visible all the time.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>
				Search
				<ul>
					<li>
						When user focuses the search input:
						<ul>
							<li>
								Add <code class="format-code">wds-search-is-active</code> class to the
								<code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation</code> element.
								It will cause the input to expand to the full width.
							</li>
							<li>
								Change input placeholder from call to action to enter search into a call to action that suggest start typing and what to search.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>
						When user clicks the X icon or presses the escape key:
						<ul>
							<li>
								Clear the input and remove <code class="format-code">wds-search-is-active</code> class.
							</li>
							<li>
								Change input placeholder to initial state.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>
						When user presses the enter key, go to the search results page with the current query.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>
				Search suggestions — their container acts similar to a dropdown
				<ul>
					<li>
						When user provides at least 3 characters, show the list of suggestions by putting them in
						<code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation__search-suggestions</code> element as a list
						and adding <code class="format-code">wds-is-active</code> class to the
						<code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation__search-input-wrapper</code> element.
					</li>
					<li>
						When user presses up or down arrow keys, highlight the currently chosen one by adding
						<code class="format-code">wds-is-selected</code> class to the proper <code class="format-code">li</code> element.
					</li>
					<li>
						When user presses the enter key while a suggestion is highlighted, go directly to the selected page.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>
				Anon and logged in state
				<ul>
					<li>
						For logged in users on tablet devices "Start a wiki" button changes into "+" icon.
						In order to make that happen <code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation__start-a-wiki</code>
						container requires additional class name: <code class="format-code">wds-user-is-logged-in</code>.
					</li>
					<li>For anon users render <code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation__account-menu</code> div that contains user login and register buttons.</li>
					<li>For logged in users render <code class="format-code">.wds-global-navigation__user-menu</code> div that contains user menu.</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

